                            <comment id="37380" author="jwunder" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2008 01:23:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Of course, an easier hack to get around the problem was to just add this statement before the buildFromName():&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;             Object o = BasePermission.WRITE;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That also forces the static initializer to execute.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39458" author="balex" created="Thu, 4 Sep 2008 15:36:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Add a PermissionTests.basePermissionTest() and reproduced the error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Removed the AbstractRegisteredPermission superclass, relocating its methods to BasePermission. This avoid superclass static initialization failures.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests all pass. Checked in as revision 3269.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
